Package: gpbiometrics
Type: Package
Title: Process and Report Gazepoint Biometrics Data
Version: 0.1.1
Authors@R: person(given = "Stefanos", family = "Balaskas", email = "s.balaskas@ac.upatras.gr", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides reproducible workflows for importing, validating, preprocessing,
    summarising, modelling, visualising, and reporting Gazepoint Biometrics
    and GP3-derived physiological exports. Supported workflows include
    heart-rate, inter-beat-interval, heart-rate-variability, pupil, gaze,
    GSR/EDA, PPG/pulse, respiration-oriented, signal-quality, synchronisation,
    windowing, artifact-detection, and multimodal reporting helpers. The
    package includes Gazepoint-native HeartPy-style pulse/PPG workflows,
    pyHRV-style HRV summaries, BioSPPy-style EDA/PPG/RRI/signal-processing
    helpers, and PsPM-style marker, SCR preprocessing, segment-extraction,
    and event-related convolution-GLM workflows, while also providing
    interoperability helpers for external psychophysiology toolchains.
